\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Result
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It was found that for a given material, the angle of repose was independent
 of the radius of the heap.
 Explicitly, change in repose angle which was expected at 
\begin_inset Formula $r/R\sim0.02$
\end_inset

 was 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 observed, where 
\begin_inset Formula $r$
\end_inset

 is the radius of the particle and 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 that of the heap.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Critique
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The experiment didn't have a well established theory backing it therefore
 it was hard to find exactly what it is that one must verify.
\end_layout

